Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place wild rice and 3 cups broth or water in casserole dish. Bake, covered, for 1.5-2 hours. Should make 3 cups cooked rice. Fry bacon until crisp. Drain off most of the grease and saute onion in remaining grease. Add half & half, mushrooms, potato soup, cooked wild rice, cheese, and 2 cups water. Heat thoroughly over low heat.